content.description: Endurance jug haul, with a steep topout.  Do not go left and skip the last bolt- it may be easier, but it's also scarier and going straight up is much more asthetic.
content.location: Pretty much in the middle of the crag.
5 feet left of "Just a Little Something".

content.description: A brilliant route that is one of the longest lines at the Minimum, and one of the best lines on the wall. It climbs the line of bolts between 49 and Just Put It In. The variation in grades is based on whether you climb straight up the bolts (12d) or whether you take a reverse "S" path wandering left towards 49 then right towards JPII.  Terrific climbing in either case.
Right of Groundwork.
content.protection: Nine bolts to two bolt anchor.

content.description: Hard start to positive holds.

This route makes a pretty good warm up.  The route still needs a bit more traffic, but the critical areas are clean.   It's overall pretty easy but gives a little crux sequence at the top to reach the   anchors.
content.location: Just to the left of Minienticer

content.description: Start just left of a deep chimney on a dark face.  Climb easy 5th class past a couple bolts to a long face that gets steeper about 2/3 the way up.  Climb past the steep section (crux) and finish at two bolts.  Climbers with good footwork won't get that warmed up on this route...if you are climbing the 12's around the corner that is.  However, an excellent and long route on its own.
content.protection: Many bolts (12-14 maybe?) to anchors with biners on them, but I'd bring two draws as backup - many biners at Maple are quite worn.
content.location: On the right side of the Minimum, uphill from Afterglow

content.description:
This is a nice pumpy route that climbs one of the few obvious features on the wall. There are a handful of moves in the lower bit of the route that are actually harder than the rest but most will cite the pump as the main difficulty.

Start up the face with some long moves on good holds or use loads of other options. Some harder moves around the 4th bolt and just before reaching the roof. Layback up the right facing corner to an alcove and rest as best you can. Bust left out the exciting undercling with your toes just at the lip of the roof. Continue in this crack as it turns to a layback then move around the arete to the anchors several feet to the left.
content.location: Find the roof that dominates the left side of the crag. This route climbs up to and laybacks past the right end of the roof before moving left around the roof to finish at anchors above the right end of the roof. Just left of 49.

content.description: Nice, continuous easy climbing.  2nd route from the left.
content.location: 2nd route from the left on the Kinder Garden wall.  Starts by ascending a small corner feature.

content.description: The Minimum is a wall of few distinguishing features, so it is difficult to describe routes other than to refer to their neighbors.  Just Put It In follows a line of bolts just right of Space Lord (3 climbs right of Lunchables, the route that goes through the right edge of the roof) and just left of Functional Idiot.  2 hard sections lead to a difficult finish straight up the black streak at the top.

The bottom of this route is full of sloping dishes on a strange for Maple, smooth wall. The upper bit climbs through the roof with some powerful climbing to start.

Move up sloping holds in the white and orange rock past the first few bolts. The climbing eases a bit above with some jugs here and there that always seem to be in the wrong place to really rest well on. Move up to the roof and rest up. Attack the roof using several small holds or a long reach to get established in the steep open corner. Move up and left out of the corner to the lip and the anchors just above.
content.location: This route goes through a vague open dihedral through the roof at the left end of the cliff. It is the second route left of Lunchables.

climbs.name: Hot Topic
climbs.fa: Glenn Ritter, Joi Matsukawa, Tommy Sutter Nov, 2015

content.description: Fun and safe beginner route.
content.location: 4th route from the left on the Kinder Garden wall.  Anchors are slightly higher than the other routes.

climbs.name: Gymboree
climbs.fa: Glenn Ritter, Joi Matsukawa, Tommy Sutter Nov, 2015

content.description: Pleasant beginner climbing
content.location: 5th route from the left on the Kinder Garden wall

content.description: On the left side of the Minimum is a pocket filled face.  Walk up the steep dirt hillside to a small belay area and climb pockets until a good no hands rest before a bulge.  Pull over the bulge past 3 more bolts to the anchors.  The long 5.9, Minienticer, is a much better warm up for the cliff.
content.protection: 7 or 8 bolts plus 2 for the anchors.
content.location: On the left side of the Minimum crag.

content.description:
Climb the first four bolts of Functional Idiot to a no hands rest on a ledge.  Break left here several feet to a separate line of bolts and commit to the steep wall above.  A few hard moves and a lot of pumpy climbing bring you to the final headwall where the line merges back into Functional Idiot for a few holds.  I looked around here and didn't see any chalk / holds for a independant line.

Clip the leftmost bolts and break left again for a decent rest before the steep wild finish past the final two bolts.  The last bolt is a bit hard to clip and easily skipped.  The fall would be long but nice and clean.
content.location: Shares first four bolts with the start of Functional Idiot.  Between "Just Put it In" and "Zoaster Toaster".

content.description: Just right of Afterglow and left of The Put Down is this fine line, which provides an excellent warmup for the harder routes on the wall.  Although still a little sandy, the route has cleaned up and gotten somewhat easier since it was bolted.  Originally rated 12b, now the grade feels closer to 11d.

Rated 12d in the guide, this route has cleaned up nicely and has gotten significantly easier.  Follow the line of bolts between Just Put It In on the left and Zoaster Toaster on the right. (FI is 4 routes right of Lunchables.) Three difficult sections separated by excellent rests, with the crux at the end.  Note that a variation called Hooked on Estrogen (12c/d?)heads up and left after the 4th bolt of Functional Idiot.
Start on Putdown and split off to the right at around 4th bolt.

This is a terrific 7 bolt extension to

Groundwork

that skirts the awesome and huge heart shaped cobble.  It is marred only by some odd bolting, for example, the only purpose of the first bolt in the cobble seems to be to provide rope drag -- skip it, its easy climbing to the next bolt, and use long draws or extensions on the first 4-5 bolts. From a hands off rest next to the huge cobble launch into a short, sequential boulder problem on bullet rock to the chains.  Excellent addition to the crag.
content.location:
From the chains atop

Groundwork

follow a line of bolts to and through the heart.

climbs.name: Children's Place
climbs.fa: Glenn Ritter, Joi Matsukawa, Tommy Sutter Nov, 2015

content.description: Climbs the clean streak in the middle of the Kinder Garden wall.  Angles slightly right at the last bolt to end at the lowering station.
content.location: Middle route on the Kinder Garden.  3rd from the left.

climbs.name: Carters
climbs.fa: Glenn Ritter, Joi Matsukawa, Tommy Sutter Nov, 2015

content.description: Furthest right route on the Kinder Garden wall.  Slightly cruxier (and shorter) than the other routes.
content.location: Furthest right (uphill) route on the Kinder Garden wall

content.description: Hard start to 5.10+ face.
This route is located between Zoaster Toaster and Afterglow.  Juggy climbing leads to a boulder problem crux at the 7th bolt followed by a pumpy finish.

14 bolts of 5.4 cobble hauling! Good fun for a first time leader or families with little ones. Left most route on the Kinder Garden wall.  Not many routes of this grade are bolted safely like this, although you still get many of the bolts at or below your feet on this long route.   Good fun!
content.protection: 14 bolts plus anchors.  Be sure to bring enough!   Recommended to stick clip the first bolt if you are a beginner leader.
content.location: The far right end of the Minimum.  Just up the hill and right of Minienticer 5.9.   This wall has 6 beginner routes from 5.4 to 5.6 which are collectively referred to the Kinder Garden.  This route is the furthest left on the wall (just right of the wide corner/crack).

content.description: The crux is about 3/4 of the way up.  Another enduro jug haul.
content.location: On the right hand side of the crag, to the right of The Big Calm.

content.description:
A great route, and one that actually holds the .12a rating.

Endurance is the name of the game; rest properly and you will send. The route stays fairly consistent the whole way; hold on.
